column10:
If you liked backpack hero and any bullet heaven game, you will enjoy this one. 

What I liked most:
1 - The sound effects of the weapons are very pleasing (specially the range ones);
2 -  The game's achievements guide you to explore what is unique in each character;
3 -  To beat the harder difficult levels you are required to understand the mechanics and items' synergies, invest in general upgrades and unlock better items.

It is on ealy access so I hope it improves even more over time. These are the aspects of the game that I think need some work at this stage:
1 - They need to allow the players to return items bought with divine favors, in case they regreat it;
2 - Don't show items that make no sense for a character (for example, why show ranged weapons in the store after each level for a character that can't use ranged weapons? or why show life stealing items for a character that can't use life stealing?)
3 - Create a few achievements for beating level 5 difficult with different characters; 
4 - Melee damage and aome melee characters need buff;
5 - Create more tags on the items (it is not very clear what counts as  what in the game).

That being said, in my opinion, the game is more than worthy for the price tag in the state that it is right now.
